Comments: Authors reported the study site at 300 masl. Elevation range reported at Bat Eco-Interactions are those reported by The IUCN Directory of Neotropical Protected Areas for Parque Nacional Santa Rosa.

Done loc & int. Coord reported for the study site within Serra de Cipo are: -19.283333 and -43.5. Habitat is described as savanna-like "cerrado" on the lower slopes, gallery forests following water courses, and the typical rocky, montane fields called "campos rupestres" on the higher portions and plateaus.  The study site is at highland-1250 masl, so it would be more accurate to assign campos rupestres-savanna for habitat type.
